comment: Phenomenal. Best Rye I've had, hands down.
Cinnamony. Decent but I don’t need a whole bottle
Very fragrant, multiple spice notes throughout. Long finish with a little heat.
Definitely a spicy kick - couldn't taste the vanilla
The best rye in its price range in the market! Great rye notes with a few hints of a sweet toffee taste.
Kinda hated this. It has a tequila sort of flavor going on.
Fantastic. Some classic rye notes but overall so easy to drink. Excellent
Great smell, taste has a little bite at first but moves into a smooth aftertaste.  Would drink it again.
Lots of brown sugar and honey notes with a spicy rye finish. Excellent!

Nose is a chocolate covered orange stick from the Rocky Mountain Chocolate Factory.

It follows through to the taste with a pleasant black pepper bit on the finish.
Heavy rye finish. Honey start noae hut goes acidic. Not my favorite. Ends with a medicine taste
Odd taste.  Not pleasant to me, but others did like it.

This rye whiskey has thick watery legs and an amber gold color.

The nose is sweet and vegetal with notes of watermelon rind, green vegetables, cooking spices, dill, juniper, wet straw, and Smarties candy.

The swallow is harsh on the back of the throat, but once you get past that, one tastes sweet notes of caramel, cinnamon, cherry candy, and kiwi.

The finish is long, sweet, and oaky. Cheers!
Not sure what others are tasting but this stuff is brutal to drink.
